The paper deals with the decomposition of channel information into synergies, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses tools from information geometry, which is a subfield of machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the modeling of a multi-input channel, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the theory of complex systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
